			<h1>The Best Traditional Moroccan Dishes</h1>

			<p>
				Live Moroccan TV |  Traditional Gnawa Music | Grilled Favorites | Tea Time & Happy Hour
			</p>
		</div>


		<div class="container text-muted">
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 ">
					<h3>Moroccan Breakfast</h3>
					<p>Start your day with the authentic flavors of Morocco. Enjoy warm msemen, fluffy baghrir, fresh khobz with olive oil and honey, and a glass of mint tea. Our breakfast menu blends tradition with taste, offering a rich and hearty morning experience.</p>

				</div>
				<div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 ">
					<h3>Moroccan Lunch

					</h3>
					<p>Discover a rich selection of traditional dishes like Couscous with vegetables, slow-cooked Tagine with chicken and preserved lemon, and spicy Mrouzia lamb. Served with fresh bread and seasonal salads for a complete and satisfying midday meal.</p>

				</div>
				<div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6">
					<h3>Moroccan Dinner
					</h3>
					<p>Enjoy a warm and flavorful Moroccan dinner with dishes like Lamb Tagine with prunes, Harira soup, and grilled kefta skewers. Complete your evening with traditional mint tea and a sweet treat like Chebakia or Sellou.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6">
					<h3>Moroccan Dessert
					</h3>
					<p>Indulge in the rich flavors of Moroccan desserts such as Baklava, Sweet Couscous, Atayef (Moroccan stuffed pancakes), and traditional Chebakia, all perfect for ending your meal on a sweet note.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>


